<item>
            <title>[LU-11782] interop: conf-sanity test 117 fails with &apos;get_param should fail&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11782</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;conf-sanity test_117 was added to the Lustre test suites to check that read_param() returns errors to the caller for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11198&quot; title=&quot;&#8220;lctl get_param&#8220; doesn&amp;#39;t return errno when reading fails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11198&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11198&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/32925&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/32925&lt;/a&gt; . This test will fail for all Lustre servers with version less than 2.12.0. Thus, we need to add a version check for conf-sanity test 117.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
